# Display — JC3248A035N-1 bare ST7796 3.5" SPI TFT (480×320)
#
# The physical display (bare glass + FPC) and all supporting circuits
# (backlight MOSFET, RC reset, bypass cap) are on the CONTROL BOARD.
# The FPC connector on the control board connects to the display glass
# sitting in the faceplate cutout.
#
# Display signals route: MCU (main board) → board connector → control board → FPC
#
# This file is kept as documentation only. No physical parts remain on the
# main board for the display — all wiring is done directly in main.ato
# (MCU signals → connector) and control.ato (connector → FPC + circuits).
#
# Display specs:
#   Part: JC3248A035N-1 (bare panel, no carrier PCB, no touch)
#   Glass: 85.5 × 54.94 × 2.5mm, active: 73.44 × 48.96mm
#   Interface: 4-wire SPI (IM pins pre-configured internally)
#   FPC: 18-pin, 0.5mm pitch, bottom edge (landscape)
#   Backlight: 4 parallel LED cathodes (K1-K4), anode to 3.3V
#   FPC pinout: 1=GND, 2=RST, 3=SCK, 4=DC, 5=CS, 6=MOSI,
#               7=MISO, 8=GND, 9=VCC, 10=LEDA, 11-14=K1-K4, 15-18=NC
